description: '''Freakbeat''' is a loosely defined subgenre of [[rock and roll]] music developed mainly by harder-driving British groups during the [[Swinging London]] period of the mid-to late 1960s. The genre bridges British Invasion [[British R&B|R&B]], [[Beat music|beat]] and [[Psychedelic rock|psychedelia]].
top_artists: Dave Dee, Dozy, Beaky, Mick & Tich
